By Onyebuchi Ezigbo in Abuja The National Chairman of the All Progressives  Congress (APC), Adams Oshiomhole, is currently in a  meeting with the Chief of Staff to the President, Abba Kyari, Governor Rochas Okorocha, Governor Abdulaziz Yari and others over issues relating to the party’s governorship and National Assembly primaries in some states. THISDAY gathered that the National Working Committee of the APC met earlier in the day to review the party primaries so far. A source told THISDAY that the party leadership, apart from approving some of the election results, appointed new a committee to conduct fresh governorship primary in Imo State.
The party has rescheduled the governorship primaries in Imo and Zamfara States to Friday. Details later…